&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.lvt.com/resources/why-work-at-lvt&quot;&gt;LVT&lt;/a&gt; is redefining how businesses operate in the physical world, moving beyond traditional security solutions to deliver AI-driven, actionable intelligence that makes sites smarter, safer, and more secure. Since pioneering our first &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.lvt.com/story&quot;&gt;mobile, solar-powered units&lt;/a&gt;, our commitment to scrappy, hands-on innovation has made us an established leader and one of the fastest-growing companies in intelligent site technology. We are building the next generation of solutions—from our physical units in the field to a powerful Agentic AI platform—that allows our customers to gain unprecedented visibility and control over safety, compliance, and operations. This is your chance to &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.lvt.com/careers&quot;&gt;join a cutting-edge team&lt;/a&gt; that isn&#39;t just watching the world change, but actively building the technology that is changing it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re a team that’s focused on growth and innovation, and we’re proud that our crew, products, and leadership are being recognized for it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Top-Tier Growth Company: &lt;/strong&gt;Named one of the &lt;em&gt;Financial Times’ Fastest Growing Companies 2025&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;#10 on the Inc. 5000 Rocky Mountain Regional&lt;/em&gt; list for 2025.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Innovative Leadership: &lt;/strong&gt;Our CEO, Ryan Porter, was named an &lt;em&gt;EY Entrepreneur of the Year 2025&lt;/em&gt;, and our CTO, Steve Lindsey, was inducted into the &lt;em&gt;Silicon Slopes CTO Hall of Fame&lt;/em&gt; in 2024.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product &amp;amp; Software Excellence: &lt;/strong&gt;We were named one of &lt;em&gt;The Software Report’s Top 100 Software Companies of 2023&lt;/em&gt; and are a winner of the &lt;em&gt;Security Today Govies Award &lt;/em&gt;for 2025.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT THIS ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Senior Director of Product Management, you will lead the strategic vision for LVT’s most critical value drivers: Intelligence and Ecosystem Delivery. Reporting directly to the Chief Product Officer, you will bridge the gap between high-level organizational goals and technical execution across our Prevent, Respond, and Recover pillars. In this role, you will also lead a high-performing team of product managers, fostering a culture of excellence and accountability while providing guidance. You are the architect of a seamless user journey—ensuring that our Edge and Cloud AI analytics translate into rapid alert management and forensic search capabilities that solve real-world problems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will be based in Seattle, WA with occasional travel to our HQ in American Fork, Utah or client sites may be required to maintain alignment and deep-market intimacy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ROLE RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Strategic Roadmap Ownership: Define and execute a multi-year product strategy for the Intelligence and Ecosystem pillars, ensuring alignment with the CPO’s vision and LVT’s overarching growth targets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;AI &amp;amp; Analytics Leadership: Drive the evolution of our &quot;Prevent&quot; capabilities, overseeing the integration of Edge and Cloud AI analytics, talkdown features, and deterrent efficacy tools.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ecosystem Integration: Lead the &quot;Respond&quot; and &quot;Recover&quot; initiatives by managing complex integrations with VMS leaders (Genetec, Milestone) and Alert Management platforms (Fusus, Immix) to ensure LVT is the central hub of site intelligence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
